ROLE: Layout Mimic + Flow Mapper for JAMstack (static HTML + Strapi).
REFERENCE (structure only, no content copy): https://www.normandpllc.com/
ASSETS: Use the two screenshots I attached as visual hints for color rhythm/spacing.
TOOLS: Firecrawl MCP, Playwright MCP, Graphviz (dot).

GOALS
1) Crawl the site (depth=2, same-origin) → output ./output/sitemap.json
2) For homepage + top-level pages:
   - Open with Playwright (1366x900), scroll to reveal lazy content
   - Do a VIPS-like segmentation into ordered “blocks” by section/bg-color/spacing
   - Save ./output/<slug>.blocks.json and ./output/<slug>.png (full-page screenshot)
3) Build a site flow graph (on-domain CTAs only) → ./output/site-flow.dot + site-flow.png
4) Generate static Tailwind HTML scaffolds (placeholders only) for each block:
   - ./scaffold/sections/<pageSlug>-block-<n>.html
   - Color mapping: black=bg-black text-white, white=bg-white text-gray-900,
     orange≈bg-orange-500 text-white, else=bg-gray-50 text-gray-900
   - Layout: max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 md:px-6, py-16 md:py-24
   - Preserve CTA counts/relative positions with generic labels (“Learn More” etc.)
5) Propose Strapi schemas (JSON drafts, not exports):
   - ./strapi/schemas/components.json → hero_section, split_media, feature_band, logo_wall, cta_band, faq_section, contact_band
     Fields: title, subtitle, rich_text, media, ctas[{label,url}], theme{bg: enum[black,white,orange,custom], invertText:boolean}
   - ./strapi/schemas/collections.json → pages{slug,title,seo,sections:dynamic zone}, navigation, settings
6) README: ./README.MIMIC.md with integration steps (Tailwind build for static HTML, mapping Strapi dynamic zones to sections), and any color approximations/ambiguous boundaries.

BLOCK EXTRACTION HEURISTICS
- Block boundary if: <section>|<header>|<main>|<footer>, bg-color change, height≥160px, or total vertical padding≥40px.
- Merge adjacent if same bg or gap<24px; skip sticky nav strips unless they are full hero.
- For each block capture:
  {
    "order": n,
    "color": "black|white|orange|<normalized rgba/hex>",
    "headingSample": "<first H1/H2/H3 or null>",
    "approxHeight": px,
    "ctas": [{"label":"Placeholder","href":"/or-absolute"}],
    "rawBg": "rgba(...)"
  }

CONSTRAINTS & ETHICS
- Do NOT copy text, images, icons, or proprietary CSS.
- Keep only structure/order/rhythm (e.g., black → orange → black → white), spacing feel, and CTA counts.

EXECUTE NOW
- Firecrawl MCP: crawl https://www.normandpllc.com/ depth=2 same-origin → save sitemap.json
- Playwright MCP: for each top page (including /), run the segmentation, save blocks.json + screenshot
- Graphviz MCP: render site-flow.dot → site-flow.png
- Generate all HTML scaffolds + Strapi schema JSON + README
- Finish with a summary per page:
  - /<slug>: N blocks, color sequence, CTA count, notes (sticky bars/modals)
